@state(version="2.0"):
phase: "implementation"
next_action: "Phase D slice 4 Phase 3 — ship `tfuneff_lambda_retype_l1_m` per `formal/SUBST-LEMMA-GENERALIZATION-DESIGN.md` §'Phase 3'. Retype lemma for TFunEff-typed lambdas (`ELam T0 e` typed at `TFunEff T1 T2 R_in R_out`) under the side condition `forall r, In r R' -> In r R_in`. Extend the Phase 2 substitution lemma to cover `T1 = TFunEff …` lambdas as substituends. The TFun (non-Eff) lambda case has body-R-rigidity (same gap as legacy preservation_l1 slice 4b) — explicitly OUT OF SCOPE for Phase 3 per design doc §'Open design questions' #2 (recommended: TFunEff only). After Phase 3, Phase 4 closes `preservation_l2`'s `T_App_L2_Eff` β-case for: (a) linear T1 via existing `subst_typing_gen_l1_m`; (b) ground non-linear T1 via Phase 2's `subst_typing_gen_l1_m_ground_nonlinear`; (c) TFunEff non-linear T1 via Phase 3; (d) compound non-linear T1 deferred to Phase 5. Anti-patterns to refuse (per CLAUDE.md owner directive): no `Admitted` to close cases; no touching `Semantics.v`/`Typing.v`/`Counterexample.v`; no closure of residual `Semantics_L1.v` admits via this work — strictly NEW infrastructure orthogonal to legacy. Coqc 8.18.0 is the only authority."
last_action: "Phase D slice 4 Phase 2 LANDED (2026-05-30): `subst_typing_gen_l1_m_ground_nonlinear` parallel substitution lemma added to `formal/Semantics_L1.v` mirroring `subst_typing_gen_l1_m`'s 28+ case structure for `is_ground_nonlinear_ty T1 = true`. Three key divergences from the linear lemma: (i) T_Var_Lin_L1 i=k0 → exfalso via `is_linear_ty Tsub = false` vs rule's premise `is_linear_ty T = true`; (ii) T_Var_Unr_L1 i=k0 → CONSTRUCTIVE case applying `ground_nonlinear_retype_l1_m` to lift Hv_type from Linear to active modality m; (iii) compound rules use `ground_nonlinear_retype_l1_m` directly (no `linear_value_is_loc_l1` / `loc_retype_at_R_l1_m` / `region_liveness_at_split_l1_gen` pipeline — ground retype takes any R, any G, any m). Phase 1's `ground_nonlinear_retype_l1_m` generalised in this PR to (m → m', R → R', G → G')-polymorphic (Phase 1 ships m-monomorphic R-only retype; Phase 2 needs the cross-modality cross-context bridge). New helper `ground_nonlinear_value_shift_id_l1` proves `shift c d v = v` for ground non-linear values; used to rewrite the `shift 0 1 vv` introduced by `subst`'s descent through term binders in T_Let_L1 / T_LetLin_L1 / T_Lam_L1_* (4 lambda rules) / T_Case_L1_* (2 case rules). Coqc 8.18.0 clean rebuild across all 10 .v files. Zero new admits/axioms. `Semantics.v`/`Typing.v`/`Counterexample.v` untouched. Phase 2 unblocks Phase 3 (TFunEff lambda retype) and Phase 4 (close preservation_l2 β-case for ground non-linear T1). Sibling-lemma approach preserves ~30 Qed downstreams of `subst_typing_gen_l1_m`."
updated: 2026-05-30T00:00:00Z

@directive(source="owner", date="2026-05-27", canonical="CLAUDE.md"):
# Captured durable directive — preservation work is the four-layer redesign,
# NOT closure of the legacy theorem. Pre-discovery patching paths are
# closed.
#
# DO NOT:
#   - close `Theorem preservation` in formal/Semantics.v (provably false)
#   - extend Semantics.v with closure-support lemmas (Lemma B variants,
#     step_preserves_type_at_pre, step_output_context_eq_at_pre,
#     region_add_typing_for_non_values, strengthened subst variants)
#   - close residual Semantics_L1.v axioms via proof tricks
#   - follow any pre-2026-05-26 "preservation closure plan"
#   - patch the legacy Typing.v judgment
#
# DO:
#   - read formal/PRESERVATION-DESIGN.md first
#   - work per-layer: preservation_l1, preservation_l2, etc.
#   - escalate before patching when a side-condition is needed
#
# Anti-pattern detector: sibling-region-disjointness side conditions,
# region-weakening predicates indexed on syntactic shape, admit-shuffling
# between Semantics.v and a new lemma. Any of these → escalate.
#
# Companion memory: feedback_ephapax_no_patching_legacy_preservation.md
@end

@blockers:
# Layered work in progress; legacy preservation deliberately not addressed.
#
# Current state (verified by coqc 8.18 on main, post-#176/#177):
#   - formal/Semantics.v `preservation`: Admitted — PROVABLY FALSE per
#     Counterexample.v (three Qed lemmas). NOT to be closed.
#   - formal/Semantics.v `step_preserves_type`, `step_output_context_eq`,
#     and their at_pre helpers are Qed but support legacy-preservation
#     closure attempts that are now ruled out. Retained for diagnostic
#     value; no new lemmas in this class.
#   - formal/Semantics_L1.v `preservation_l1`: stated `forall m`; body
#     Admitted (lambda-rigidity gap, closes at Phase D / L2 effect-typed
#     TFun per PRESERVATION-DESIGN.md §5.1). 5 inner `admit.` cases
#     (3 distinct structural blockers + 2 mechanical mirrors) covered
#     by 3 outer Admitted markers. Zero new debt introduced post-L2.
#   - formal/Semantics_L1.v `preservation_l3`: Qed, both modes, slice 4
#     of L3 wiring landed 2026-05-27 (PR #196).
#   - formal/TypingL1.v: m-indexed (`has_type_l1 m R G e T R' G'`),
#     `linear_to_affine` Qed zero axioms; T_Echo_L1 / T_Observe_L1 +
#     parallel T_*_Echo rules landed for L3 wiring;
#     T_Lam_L1_*_Eff (slice 2) produce TFunEff lambdas; T_App_L1
#     requires TFun (not TFunEff), so TFunEff lambdas are inert at
#     L1 — their elimination form lives at L2 via T_App_L2_Eff
#     (PR #209, option 5a).
#   - formal/TypingL2.v: post-#209/#211 has TWO constructors —
#     L2_lift_l1 (any L1 derivation) and T_App_L2_Eff (effect-typed
#     application, Phase D slice 3). project_l2_to_l1 now
#     option-returning; weaken_modality proof by structural
#     induction. Post-#211: `preservation_l2_via_l1` +
#     `preservation_l2_lift_case` corollary land the L2_lift_l1
#     case of preservation_l2 (depends transparently on
#     `Semantics_L1.preservation_l1` admit via Print Assumptions).
#     Full preservation_l2 over has_type_l2 blocked at T_App_L2_Eff
#     β-case on `subst_typing_gen_l1_m`'s linearity precondition.
#     All Qed, zero new axioms in TypingL2.v.
#   - formal/Echo.v: K-free L3 calculus, no postulates, 12 Qed.
#   - formal/Modality.v: thin-poset Linear ≤ Affine, all Qed.
#   - formal/L4.v: ProgramMode labelling discipline, Definitions only,
#     no theorems. Phase A landed 2026-05-28.
#
# Other proof-debt items (out of preservation scope):
#   - src/abi/Ephapax/ABI/Invariants.idr E1-E6: E1 (preservation) OWED at
#     the Idris2 layer too; E2/E3 PARTIAL; E4/E5/E6 OWED.
#   - 30 unsafe Rust blocks; per-block contract audit out of scope.
@end

